    old "She jumped out of the bed, gathered what little she could."
    new "She jumped out of the bed, gathered what little she could."

    old "The voices came nearer and nearer."
    new "The voices came nearer and nearer."

    old "Run. She had to run now."
    new "Run. She had to run now."

    old "Sarah turned the corner, away from the voices."
    new "Sarah turned the corner, away from the voices."

    old "Guard Captain\" \"There she goes!"
    new "Guard Captain\" \"There she goes!"

    old "Sarah heard his voice calling after her."
    new "Sarah heard his voice calling after her."

    old "The sounds of metal boots, pounding on cobblestone as they began to chase her."
    new "The sounds of metal boots, pounding on cobblestone as they began to chase her."

    old "Sarah broke into a sprint."
    new "Sarah broke into a sprint."

    old "The violent sounds of their pursuit echoed through the small alley."
    new "The violent sounds of their pursuit echoed through the small alley."

    old "She felt her heart pounding in her chest as she began to ran faster and faster."
    new "She felt her heart pounding in her chest as she began to ran faster and faster."

    old "Her feet were stomping the ground, carrying her body as fast as she could manage."
    new "Her feet were stomping the ground, carrying her body as fast as she could manage."

    old "Run. Run. Faster. Run."
    new "Run. Run. Faster. Run."

    old "She had never run so fast in all her life."
    new "She had never run so fast in all her life."

    old "Behind her, their voices, growing louder."
    new "Behind her, their voices, growing louder."

    old "Closer."
    new "Closer."

    old "Run. Faster. Run. Faster."
    new "Run. Faster. Run. Faster."

    old "Sarah felt her vision go blurry."
    new "Sarah felt her vision go blurry."

    old "She dared not to even look back as she ran."
    new "She dared not to even look back as she ran."

    old "Their voices so near, she was sure they'd grab her if she was even slow for a moment."
    new "Their voices so near, she was sure they'd grab her if she was even slow for a moment."

    old "She ducked into another alley, sprinting as fast as she could."
    new "She ducked into another alley, sprinting as fast as she could."

    old "The space around her rushed by, unfamiliar places she had never been before."
    new "The space around her rushed by, unfamiliar places she had never been before."

    old "Poor folk that inhabited the back alleys of Lethram, looked on in surprise."
    new "Poor folk that inhabited the back alleys of Lethram, looked on in surprise."

    old "They were no strangers so guards chasing people, but none of them had ever seen them give chase to a proper rich girl before."
    new "They were no strangers so guards chasing people, but none of them had ever seen them give chase to a proper rich girl before."

    old "But most only looked on bemused."
    new "But most only looked on bemused."

    old "They didn't care enough to stop her. Nor enough to help."
    new "They didn't care enough to stop her. Nor enough to help."

    old "Behind her, the ever approaching voices and sounds of the city guard."
    new "Behind her, the ever approaching voices and sounds of the city guard."

    old "Guards\" \"Stop! Thief!"
    new "Guards\" \"Stop! Thief!"

    old "Sounds of their blades being drawn."
    new "Sounds of their blades being drawn."

    old "Sarah felt panic rush over her."
    new "Sarah felt panic rush over her."

    old "Kill her. They might actually kill her."
    new "Kill her. They might actually kill her."

    old "The pure fear pumped her body with adrenaline."
    new "The pure fear pumped her body with adrenaline."

    old "And she ran faster than she had ever ran."
    new "And she ran faster than she had ever ran."

    old "The whole world a blur, only the forward motion."
    new "The whole world a blur, only the forward motion."

    old "The streets rushed by, the faces of the people, nothing."
    new "The streets rushed by, the faces of the people, nothing."

    old "She would remember nothing."
    new "She would remember nothing."

    old "There was only the run."
    new "There was only the run."

    old "Sarah felt the stinging pain of the cobblestone cutting through her shoes."
    new "Sarah felt the stinging pain of the cobblestone cutting through her shoes."

    old "Still, her body kept going."
    new "Still, her body kept going."

    old "Suddenly, she stumbled out from the alley."
    new "Suddenly, she stumbled out from the alley."

    old "All about her, the bustling city, merchants and craftsmen, rising for an early morning."
    new "All about her, the bustling city, merchants and craftsmen, rising for an early morning."

    old "She looked about in a panic."
    new "She looked about in a panic."

    old "Behind her, the approaching guards."
    new "Behind her, the approaching guards."

    old "Sarah saw some looking at her with a worried expression."
    new "Sarah saw some looking at her with a worried expression."

    old "No time."
    new "No time."

    old "She began to run again."
    new "She began to run again."

    old "Taking off in a mad sprint, she dashed in between the sprawling crowd."
    new "Taking off in a mad sprint, she dashed in between the sprawling crowd."

    old "Behind her, the sounds of the guards grew ever more distant."
    new "Behind her, the sounds of the guards grew ever more distant."

    old "They yelled, screamed, ran."
    new "They yelled, screamed, ran."

    old "But their armor too slow."
    new "But their armor too slow."

    old "And Sarah, too nimble, as she darted in between the masses."
    new "And Sarah, too nimble, as she darted in between the masses."

    old "Faster. Always faster."
    new "Faster. Always faster."

    old "Her entire body felt as if it was on fire, but still she kept going."
    new "Her entire body felt as if it was on fire, but still she kept going."

    old "Down the street."
    new "Down the street."

    old "Take a turn, up along the avenue, across a market."
    new "Take a turn, up along the avenue, across a market."

    old "Sarah couldn't remember how far she'd ran, only that she was entirely lost."
    new "Sarah couldn't remember how far she'd ran, only that she was entirely lost."

    old "But direction didn't seem to mean anything."
    new "But direction didn't seem to mean anything."

    old "The only thing that mattered was getting away from the guards."
    new "The only thing that mattered was getting away from the guards."

    old "Finally, when she could no longer hear the voices, Sarah turned."
    new "Finally, when she could no longer hear the voices, Sarah turned."

